    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-meat-free-chick-n-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-meat-free-chick-n-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the<strong> halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min further or until starting to break down</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-meat-free-chick-n-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p><p>Chop any larger pieces of your <strong>meat-free chick'n</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-meat-free-chick-n-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes have started to break down, add the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>to the pan with your <strong>garam masala</strong>,<strong> ground fenugreek</strong> and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>paprika</strong> and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-meat-free-chick-n-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, raise the heat to medium-high add your <strong>meat-free chick'n</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min or until warmed through</p><p>Tip: Add an extra drizzle of vegetable oil if the meat-free chick'n is looking a little dry!</p><p>Once the meat-free chick'n<strong> </strong>is warmed through, add the <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>warming</strong> <strong>meat-free chick'n bhuna</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-meat-free-chick-n-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the meat-free bhuna is cooking, chop your<strong> coriander</strong> finely</p><p>Add your <strong>garlic & coriander naan[s]</strong> to a <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/warming-meat-free-chick-n-bhuna-with-brown-rice-and-naan/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>warming</strong> <strong>meat-free chick'n</strong> <strong>bhuna</strong> with the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>naan </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
